The US is changing the rules for obtaining a visa
The persons must present themselves for visa applications before their consulate talks with the service providers; the costs will be reduced accordingly.
As from 10 January 2011, the procedures for requesting a visa will be amended in the United States Embassy and Consulates.
In the new procedure, most applicants must present themselves before their consultation with the visa application services (ASC, the initial letters in English).
The ASC staff shall record the applicant's biometric data checked by the Consulate prior to the discussion.
The new procedure has certain advantages for the aspirants, including:
The total cost of processing the visa is reduced, as there is no longer a need to pay separately the appointment agreement, the processing of the visa application and the transport service with which the document is handed out.
The applicant shall make only one payment covering the three services.
The current price remains unchanged: the equivalent of 140 dollars for a tourist visa, 150 dollars for visas with application (including visas for temporary workers) and 390 dollars for hands and investors.
Those who just want to extend their visa need not have a conversation in the consulate, they only have to introduce themselves to the nearest ASC, where they present their documents and their fingerprints are taken.
As the biometric data are collected in the ASC, the applicants who need a second date for the consultation at the Consulate remain there less time than before.
Those who apply for the visa in the Consulates of Ciudad Juárez, Monterrey and Nuevo Laredo will no longer have to pay the order of 26 dollars.
Additional information on the new visa application procedure can be found on the following website: http://mexico.usembassy.gov/boletines/sp101201_Visas-FAQs.html
